# 💻 Real-World Example (Python + Flask + AWS)

Suppose you build a Flask API.

### Flask API

```python
from flask import Flask

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route('/')
def home():
    return "Welcome to EduArn"

if __name__ == "__main__":
    app.run()
```

### Git Workflow

```bash
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Created Flask API"
```

### AWS Deployment Workflow

1. Push code to GitHub
2. Pull code on AWS EC2
3. Run Flask application
4. Make API accessible publicly

Git becomes the bridge between local development and cloud deployment.

